Atotal of 24 lives were lost in various fire incidents in Katsina State in 2021. The state Chief Fire Officer, Lawal Saulawa, who stated this in Katsina on Wednesday, added that property and goods estimated at N600m were destroyed in the incidents. He revealed that the fire service saved 45 lives and salvaged property worth N2bn during the period. According to Saulawa, 568 fire incidents were recorded in the 34 local government areas of the state in 2021. “We will not cease with our enlightenment campaigns on the need for people to be careful with fire, especially during the harmattan. We are also urging people to promptly report any fire incident,” he added. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com